* `%s` reads **until the next whitespace** without any length limit.  
* If any field in the log line exceeds the size of the destination buffer (`entry.ip`, `entry.method`, `entry.url`, `entry.user_agent`), `sscanf` will write past the buffer boundary → **buffer overflow**.

